Myth: Eating raw oysters is safe if you drown them in hot sauce, which<br>k=
ills everything.=0D<br>Fact: The active ingredients in hot sauce have no mo=
re effect on<br>harmful bacteria than plain water. Nothing but prolonged ex=
posure to<br>heat at a high enough temperature will kill bacteria.=0D<br>=0D=
<br>Myth: Avoid oysters from polluted waters and you'll be fine.=0D<br>Fact=
: Many pathogens in oysters have nothing to do with pollution.<br>Some harm=
ful bacteria thrive naturally in warm coastal areas (such as<br>the Gulf of=
 Mexico) where oysters live.=0D<br>=0D<br>Myth: An experienced oyster lover=
 can tell a good oyster from a bad<br>one.=0D<br>Fact: These pathogens can'=
t be seen, smelled, or even tasted. Don't<br>rely on your senses to decide =
if an oyster is safe.=0D<br>=0D<br>Myth: Alcohol kills harmful organisms.=0D=
<br>Fact: Alcohol may impair your good judgment, but it doesn't destroy<br>=
